
README – SOAR Playbook Development
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates a Security Orchestration, Automation, and Response (SOAR) playbook for handling phishing incidents. The playbook automates threat validation, IP blocking, and incident creation.

🎯 Objective

To design and simulate an automated response workflow for phishing alerts using:

Splunk Phantom (concept)
TheHive (case management)
CrowdSec (IP blocking)
🧰 Tools Used
Splunk Phantom (simulated)
TheHive (simulated)
CrowdSec (simulated)
Google Docs (documentation)
🔄 Playbook Workflow
Receive phishing alert
Check IP reputation
Block malicious IP
Create incident case
Notify analyst
📊 Playbook Execution
Playbook Step	Status	Notes
Check IP	Success	IP flagged as malicious
Block IP	Success	Blocked 192.168.1.102
Create Case	Success	Incident recorded
Notify User	Success	Analyst informed
🧠 Conclusion

The playbook successfully automated phishing response, reducing manual effort and improving response speed.

📄 REPORT (SUBMIT THIS)
🔹 Playbook Summary (50 words)

A SOAR playbook was developed to automate phishing incident response. The workflow includes validating IP reputation, blocking malicious IPs, creating incident tickets, and notifying analysts. The simulation demonstrated successful execution of all steps, improving response efficiency and ensuring consistent handling of phishing-related threats in a SOC environment.
